Class InfectionGraph

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.miracosta.cs113.InfectionGraph

  • public class InfectionGraph
extends java.lang.Object
    InfectionGraph Class that will be what holds an instance of ListGraph and does all the necessary actions to create a Graph. Then manipulates the Graph with the use of dijkstra's algorithm for use in our Infection.

    • Constructor Detail

      • InfectionGraph

        public InfectionGraph()
        Default Constructor. Will use the default input file for initializing the graph. Will then set the length of our predecessors and distances arrays to match the number of vertices in our graph. Post: cityNames array filled with cities from file. infectionGraph has been initialized from file. predecessors and distances array have been initialized to proper size(matching the number of vertices)

      • InfectionGraph

        public InfectionGraph(java.lang.String inputFileName)
        Constructor that will use the passed in file name to create our ListGraph. Pre: That the file is in the proper format for loading edges from file described in AbstractGraph class's createGraph method. Post: cityNames array filled with cities from file. infectionGraph has been initialized from file. predecessors and distances array have been initialized to proper size(matching the number of vertices)
        Parameters:
        inputFileName - String that will correspond to the properly formatted file to create our graph from.

      • getRating

        public java.lang.String[][] getRating()
        Calculate and return the rating in a sorted order for the distances that were previously calculated using dijkstra's. Pre: Dijkstra's has been run prior to this method being called.
        Returns:
        String[][] of formatted distances and city names in order of least to greatest distance.

      • printShortestPath

        public void printShortestPath()
        A method to print out the results after dijkstra's has been ran and stored within distances and predecessors arrays. Pre: Dijkstra's has been ran therefore graph has been created and both predecessor and distances arrays have been populated. Post: The shortest path has been printed out to the screen.

      • printShortestPathWithCityNames

        public void printShortestPathWithCityNames()
        A method to print out the results after dijkstra's has been ran and stored within distances and predecessors arrays. Pre: Dijkstra's has been ran therefore graph has been created and both predecessor and distances arrays have been populated. City Names must currently be stored in cityNames array as well. Assume that loadCitiesFromFile has been called. Post: The shortest path has been printed out to the screen with city names instead of indices.

      • printPathToDestination

        public int[] printPathToDestination(int destination)
        Print the path to a desired destination. Returns an int[] of the path from the start to the destination. Pre: Only works if dijkstra's has already been ran therefore predecessors and distances arrays have been filled.
        Parameters:
        destination - int of the destination you want to get to.
        Returns:
        int[] an array of int's storing the path to the destination.
